## Code Quality Rules

### 1. Remove Unused Code

- Remove unused files, folders, and components after cleanup
- Delete unused imports and variables
- Remove commented-out code

### 2. Design Patterns & Architecture

- Develop the project using senior-level design patterns
- Make the project maintainable and scalable
- Use proper separation of concerns
- Follow React best practices (hooks, context, custom hooks)

### 3. Constants Management

- Move all static variables, magic numbers, and hardcoded strings to constants file
- Use constants from `@constants` instead of hardcoding values
- Extract repeated format functions to use hooks (`useCurrencyFormatter`, `useDateFormatter`)

### 4. Code Organization

- Use path aliases (`@components`, `@utils`, `@constants`, etc.)
- Group related functionality together
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Also Maintain the Reuseablility of Component.

### 5. Error Handling

- Replace console.log/warn with proper error handling
- Use error boundaries where appropriate
- Provide user-friendly error messages
